{"lemma":"باقِيَةُ","slug":"باقِيَةُ","root":"ب.ق.#","root_slug":"ب-ق-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ق-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"باقِيَةُ","root":"بقي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3055"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":["/baː.qiː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3055","headword_ar":"بَاقِيَةٌ","root":"bqY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAqiyaAtu AlS~aAliHaAtu","text_ar":"البَاقِيَاتُ الصَّالِحَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur xviii. 44, and xix. 79,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any righteous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the recompense remains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acts of obedience,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":239},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xix. 79,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good works,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xviii. 44,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the fruit remains for ever:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in both those places, and Jel * in the former:) and, as included therein, [so Bd, but in the K “ or, ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the five prayers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the performance of the pilgrimage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the keeping the fast of Ramadán;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xviii. 44;) and [so Bd, but in the K “ or, ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa AlHamodulil~`hi wa laA A_il~aA A@ll~`hu wa A@ll~`hu A^akobaru","text_ar":"وَ الحَمْدُلِلّٰهِ وَ لَا اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ وَ ا@للّٰهُ اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Bd and Jel in xviii. 44, and K;) to which some add,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa laA Hawola","text_ar":"وَ لَا حَوْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa laA quw~apa A_il~aA biA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"وَ لَا قُوَّةَ اـِلَّا بِا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Jel ibid.:) or, accord. to Er-Rághib, the correct meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any religious service whereby one seeks to obtain the recompense of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last explanation. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqiyapN","text_ar":"بَاقِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes put in the place of an inf. n.; (S, K;) or it is an inf. n.; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaA='N","text_ar":"بَقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, TA;) with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apN","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is syn. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srE","text_ar":"سرع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) So in the Kur [lxix. 8],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahalo taraY lahumo mino baAqiyapK","text_ar":"فَهَلْ تَرَى لَهُمْ مِنْ بَاقِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And dost thou see them to have any continuance?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) so says Fr: (TA:) or, as some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~apK","text_ar":"بَقِيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a remnant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEapK baAqiyapK","text_ar":"جَمَاعَةٍ بَاقِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company remaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Er-Rághib, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosK baAqiyapK","text_ar":"نَفْسٍ بَاقِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person, remaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Bd, Jel:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an intensive affix; (Jel;) [or a restrictive to unity;] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one remaining;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, TA;) and this is also allowable and good: one says, likewise,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baqiyato baAqiyapN wa laA wa qaAhumo mina A@ll~`hi waAqiyapN","text_ar":"مَا بَقِيَتْ بَاقِيَةٌ وَ لَا وَ قَاهُمْ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ وَاقِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One remaining remained not, nor did one preserver preserve them from God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Bd","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}